tream dependency issue caused by adservice.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on the anomaly metrics data retrieved for the UUID 980853cb-240, I analyzed the key metrics and entities involved during the reported fault from 2025-06-12T11:02:54Z to 2025-06-12T11:17:54Z.\n\n### Analysis\n\n#### Key Anomalies\nAmong the metrics, notable changes in Node-level resource utilization were observed, specifically:\n\n1. **Node Memory Usage Rate**:\n   - **aiops-k8s-01** showed a significant increase from 38.38% to 68.2% in memory usage rate.\n   - **aiops-k8s-08** increased from 53.22% to 76.35%.\n   - Similarly, **aiops-k8s-04** and **aiops-k8s-05** exhibited concerning changes in memory usage.\n\n2. **Additional Node Indicators**:\n   - **aiops-k8s-03** showed CPU usage rate increase from 32.58% to 49.71%.\n   - **aiops-k8s-04** and **aiops-k8s-08** displayed decreased memory available bytes.\n\n### Conclusions\n1. **Node-Level Primary Culprit**:\n   - The dominant contributor to the anomaly appears to be memory limitations on several nodes, especially **aiops-k8s-08**.\n  \n2. **Service-Level Symptom Recognition**:\n   - High response time ratios and errors were detected in services running on these affected nodes, which is consequent and symptomatic of underlying node stress, aligning with detected memory pressures.\n\n3. **Assumptions & Verifications**:\n   - The detected high `node_memory_usage_rate` across multiple nodes, particularly **aiops-k8s-08**, strongly suggests node resource exhaustion as the root cause rather than isolated service failures. \n\n### JSON Output\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\",\n    \"node_memory_usage_rate\",\n    \"node_cpu_usage_rate\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-08\",\n      \"reason\": \"Memory exhaustion causing degradation across services hosted on this node.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_memor